      "content": "I am sorry to hear your flight to Singapore has been cancelled; it is a very stressful situation. Since you are at Terminal 5, you should immediately head to the airline's customer service desk or the Heathrow Information desk to confirm your new options. Many airlines have specific procedures for rebooking passengers on cancelled flights, and they will often assist you in finding the quickest available connection. Please keep your boarding pass and identification ready, as you may need to show them to access priority rebooking lines. While you wait for assistance, try to stay calm and keep your phone charged, as you will need it to check real-time flight updates. If the airport provides a hotel voucher or meal vouchers due to the cancellation, ensure you collect them promptly to avoid losing them. Remember that even though the situation is chaotic, the airport staff there are trained to help you navigate the process efficiently.",
